      <h2 class="charm-text">Scouting in Ames, Iowa</h2>
      <p>
        Ames, Iowa is home to several active Scouting groups, with Cub Scout packs for children in elementary school, and Scouts BSA troops for middle and high school youth. So there's a place for your child at every age. Cub Scouts is one of the few activities the whole family can do together with campouts, hikes, service projects, and den meetings designed with parents in on the fun, not just watching from the sidelines. In Scouts BSA troops, your children learn leadership and responsibility by planning their own activities. 
      </p>
      <p>  
        Along the way, your child builds confidence, makes lasting friendships, and develops real skills from first aid to woodworking (there are over 135 merit badges to choose from). The fun has a purpose: Scouting America's program is built around character, leadership, fitness, and citizenship, helping kids grow into capable, kind, prepared adults. 
      </p>
      <p>  
        Whether you have a kindergartner who loves to explore or a teenager ready to lead, an Ames pack or troop is ready to welcome your family.
      </p>

